{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I'm Jane McGonigal. I'm a game designer."},{"time":2246,"text":"I've been making games\nonline now for 10 years,"},{"time":5000,"text":"and my goal for the next decade"},{"time":8000,"text":"is to try to make it as easy\nto save the world in real life"},{"time":13420,"text":"as it is to save the world\nin online games."},{"time":16626,"text":"Now, I have a plan for this,"},{"time":18641,"text":"and it entails convincing more people,"},{"time":21578,"text":"including all of you, to spend more time\nplaying bigger and better games."}]},{"cues":[{"time":26459,"text":"Right now we spend three billion hours\na week playing online games."},{"time":31357,"text":"Some of you might be thinking,"},{"time":33000,"text":"\"That's a lot of time\nto spend playing games."},{"time":35167,"text":"Maybe too much time,"},{"time":36493,"text":"considering how many urgent problems\nwe have to solve in the real world.\""},{"time":40000,"text":"But actually, according to my research\nat the Institute for the Future,"},{"time":44000,"text":"actually the opposite is true."},{"time":47000,"text":"Three billion hours a week\nis not nearly enough game play"},{"time":50349,"text":"to solve the world's most urgent problems."}]},{"cues":[{"time":52771,"text":"In fact, I believe\nthat if we want to survive"},{"time":55414,"text":"the next century on this planet,"},{"time":57000,"text":"we need to increase\nthat total dramatically."},{"time":59547,"text":"I've calculated the total we need"},{"time":61549,"text":"at 21 billion hours\nof game play every week."},{"time":65547,"text":"So, that's probably a bit\nof a counter-intuitive idea,"},{"time":68213,"text":"so I'll say it again, let it sink in:"},{"time":70778,"text":"If we want to solve problems like hunger,"},{"time":73000,"text":"poverty, climate change,\nglobal conflict, obesity,"},{"time":76270,"text":"I believe that we need to aspire\nto play games online"},{"time":80310,"text":"for at least 21 billion hours a week,\nby the end of the next decade."}]},{"cues":[{"time":83906,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":84938,"text":"No. I'm serious. I am."}]},{"cues":[{"time":87080,"text":"Here's why."},{"time":88255,"text":"This picture pretty much sums up\nwhy I think games are so essential"},{"time":91522,"text":"to the future survival\nof the human species."}]},{"cues":[{"time":93685,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":94713,"text":"Truly."},{"time":95888,"text":"This is a portrait\nby photographer Phil Toledano."},{"time":98529,"text":"He wanted to capture\nthe emotion of gaming,"},{"time":100793,"text":"so he set up a camera in front\nof gamers while they were playing."},{"time":103927,"text":"And this is a classic gaming emotion."},{"time":106876,"text":"Now, if you're not a gamer,"},{"time":108805,"text":"you might miss some\nof the nuance in this photo."},{"time":111226,"text":"You probably see the sense of urgency,"},{"time":114000,"text":"a little bit of fear,\nbut intense concentration,"},{"time":117408,"text":"deep, deep focus on tackling\na really difficult problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":121000,"text":"If you are a gamer, you will notice\na few nuances here:"},{"time":124761,"text":"the crinkle of the eyes up,\nand around the mouth"},{"time":127574,"text":"is a sign of optimism,"},{"time":129193,"text":"and the eyebrows up is surprise."},{"time":131652,"text":"This is a gamer who's on the verge\nof something called an \"epic win.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":135803,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":137000,"text":"Oh, you've heard of that."},{"time":138430,"text":"OK, good, so we have some gamers among us."},{"time":140986,"text":"An epic win is an outcome\nthat is so extraordinarily positive,"},{"time":145256,"text":"you had no idea it was even\npossible until you achieved it."},{"time":148296,"text":"It was almost beyond the threshold\nof imagination, and when you get there,"},{"time":152579,"text":"you're shocked to discover\nwhat you're truly capable of."},{"time":155262,"text":"That's an epic win."},{"time":156444,"text":"This is a gamer on the verge\nof an epic win."},{"time":158852,"text":"And this is the face that we need to see"},{"time":161289,"text":"on millions of problem-solvers\nall over the world"},{"time":164000,"text":"as we try to tackle the obstacles\nof the next century --"},{"time":167345,"text":"the face of someone who, against all odds,"},{"time":170000,"text":"is on the verge of an epic win."}]},{"cues":[{"time":171921,"text":"Now, unfortunately this is more\nof the face that we see"},{"time":175261,"text":"in everyday life now as we try\nto tackle urgent problems."},{"time":178056,"text":"This is what I call\nthe \"I'm Not Good At Life\" face."},{"time":180579,"text":"This is actually me making it."},{"time":182103,"text":"Can you see? Yes. Good."},{"time":183380,"text":"This is me making\nthe \"I'm Not Good At Life\" face."},{"time":186000,"text":"This is a piece of graffiti\nin my old neighborhood"},{"time":188405,"text":"in Berkeley, California,\nwhere I did my PhD"},{"time":190684,"text":"on why we're better in games\nthan we are in real life."},{"time":193922,"text":"And this is a problem\nthat a lot of gamers have."},{"time":196225,"text":"We feel that we are not as good\nin reality as we are in games."}]},{"cues":[{"time":200526,"text":"I don't mean just good as in successful,\nalthough that's part of it."},{"time":204000,"text":"We do achieve more in game worlds."},{"time":205869,"text":"But I also mean good as in motivated\nto do something that matters --"},{"time":209859,"text":"inspired to collaborate and to cooperate."},{"time":212667,"text":"And when we're in game worlds,"},{"time":214143,"text":"I believe that many of us become\nthe best version of ourselves --"},{"time":217224,"text":"the most likely to help\nat a moment's notice,"},{"time":219366,"text":"the most likely to stick\nwith a problem as long at it takes,"},{"time":222231,"text":"to get up after failure and try again."},{"time":224341,"text":"And in real life, when we face failure,"},{"time":228000,"text":"when we confront obstacles,\nwe often don't feel that way."},{"time":230914,"text":"We feel overcome, we feel overwhelmed,"},{"time":233780,"text":"we feel anxious, maybe depressed,\nfrustrated or cynical."},{"time":237544,"text":"We never have those feelings\nwhen we're playing games,"},{"time":240124,"text":"they just don't exist in games."},{"time":241687,"text":"So that's what I wanted to study\nwhen I was a graduate student."}]},{"cues":[{"time":244768,"text":"What about games makes it impossible"},{"time":247264,"text":"to feel that we can't achieve everything?"},{"time":249741,"text":"How can we take those feelings from games"},{"time":252169,"text":"and apply them to real-world work?"},{"time":253856,"text":"So I looked at games\nlike World of Warcraft,"},{"time":256278,"text":"which is really the ideal collaborative\nproblem-solving environment."},{"time":259587,"text":"And I started to notice a few things"},{"time":261435,"text":"that make epic wins\nso possible in online worlds."}]},{"cues":[{"time":264616,"text":"The first thing is whenever you show up\nin one of these online games,"},{"time":267925,"text":"especially in World of Warcraft,"},{"time":269528,"text":"there are lots and lots\nof different characters"},{"time":271846,"text":"who are willing to trust you\nwith a world-saving mission, right away."},{"time":276124,"text":"But not just any mission,"},{"time":277649,"text":"it's a mission that is perfectly matched\nwith your current level in the game."},{"time":281489,"text":"Right? So you can do it."},{"time":283219,"text":"They never give you a challenge\nyou can't achieve."},{"time":285688,"text":"But it is on the verge\nof what you're capable of,"},{"time":288087,"text":"so you have to try hard."},{"time":289355,"text":"But there's no unemployment\nin World of Warcraft; no sitting around,"},{"time":292700,"text":"wringing your hands --"},{"time":293875,"text":"there's always something\nspecific and important to be done."},{"time":296718,"text":"There are also tons of collaborators."},{"time":298575,"text":"Everywhere you go,\nhundreds of thousands of people"},{"time":300987,"text":"ready to work with you\nto achieve your epic mission."}]},{"cues":[{"time":303953,"text":"That's not something we have\nin real life that easily,"},{"time":306603,"text":"this sense that at our fingertips\nare tons of collaborators."},{"time":309616,"text":"And there's this epic story,\nthis inspiring story of why we're there,"},{"time":313131,"text":"and what we're doing,"},{"time":314316,"text":"and we get all this positive feedback."},{"time":316218,"text":"You guys have heard of leveling up,\n+1 strength, +1 intelligence."},{"time":320235,"text":"We don't get that kind\nof constant feedback in real life."},{"time":322941,"text":"When I get off this stage,"},{"time":324206,"text":"I'm not going to have\n+1 speaking, and +1 crazy idea,"},{"time":329112,"text":"+20 crazy idea."},{"time":330800,"text":"I don't get that feedback in real life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":332842,"text":"Now, the problem with collaborative\nonline environments like World of Warcraft"},{"time":337714,"text":"is that it's so satisfying to be\non the verge of an epic win all the time,"},{"time":341893,"text":"we decide to spend all our time\nin these game worlds."},{"time":344492,"text":"It's just better than reality."},{"time":346000,"text":"So, so far, collectively\nall the World of Warcraft gamers"},{"time":349000,"text":"have spent 5.93 million years"},{"time":352000,"text":"solving the virtual problems of Azeroth."},{"time":356000,"text":"Now, that's not necessarily a bad thing."},{"time":358517,"text":"It might sound like it's a bad thing."},{"time":360400,"text":"But to put that in context:"},{"time":361748,"text":"5.93 million years ago"},{"time":363855,"text":"was when our earliest primate\nhuman ancestors stood up."},{"time":368504,"text":"That was the first upright primate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":371258,"text":"So when we talk about how much time"},{"time":374386,"text":"we're currently investing\nin playing games,"},{"time":376422,"text":"the only way it makes sense\nto even think about it"},{"time":379224,"text":"is to talk about time\nat the magnitude of human evolution,"},{"time":383000,"text":"which is an extraordinary thing."},{"time":385000,"text":"But it's also apt,"},{"time":386532,"text":"because it turns out that by spending\nall this time playing games,"},{"time":389714,"text":"we're actually changing\nwhat we are capable of as human beings."},{"time":393000,"text":"We're evolving to be a more\ncollaborative and hearty species."},{"time":396663,"text":"This is true. I believe this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":398449,"text":"So, consider this really\ninteresting statistic;"},{"time":401314,"text":"it was recently published by a researcher\nat Carnegie Mellon University:"},{"time":404822,"text":"The average young person today\nin a country with a strong gamer culture"},{"time":409000,"text":"will have spent 10,000 hours\nplaying online games"},{"time":412678,"text":"by the age of 21."},{"time":414439,"text":"Now 10,000 hours is a really\ninteresting number for two reasons."},{"time":418420,"text":"First of all, for children\nin the United States,"},{"time":421890,"text":"10,080 hours is the exact amount\nof time you will spend in school,"},{"time":426898,"text":"from fifth grade\nto high school graduation,"},{"time":429024,"text":"if you have perfect attendance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":430571,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":431596,"text":"So, we have an entire\nparallel track of education going on,"},{"time":435205,"text":"where young people are learning as much\nabout what it takes to be a good gamer"},{"time":438937,"text":"as they're learning\nabout everything else in school."},{"time":441441,"text":"Some of you have probably read\nMalcolm Gladwell's new book \"Outliers,\""},{"time":445052,"text":"so you would have heard\nof his theory of success,"},{"time":447418,"text":"the \"10,000 hours\" theory of success."},{"time":449541,"text":"It's based on this great\ncognitive-science research"},{"time":452000,"text":"that says if we can master 10,000 hours"},{"time":455341,"text":"of effortful study at anything\nby the age of 21,"},{"time":458738,"text":"we will be virtuosos at it."},{"time":460261,"text":"We will be as good at whatever we do"},{"time":462000,"text":"as the greatest people in the world."},{"time":463865,"text":"And so, now what we're looking at"},{"time":466647,"text":"is an entire generation of young people\nwho are virtuoso gamers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":471758,"text":"So, the big question is,"},{"time":474000,"text":"\"What exactly are gamers\ngetting so good at?\""},{"time":477341,"text":"Because if we could figure that out,"},{"time":479150,"text":"we would have a virtually unprecedented\nhuman resource on our hands."},{"time":483579,"text":"This is how many people\nwe now have in the world"},{"time":485866,"text":"who spend at least an hour\na day playing online games."},{"time":488777,"text":"These are our virtuoso gamers,"},{"time":490897,"text":"500 million people who are\nextraordinarily good at something."},{"time":495658,"text":"And in the next decade,"},{"time":497000,"text":"we're going to have another billion gamers"},{"time":499024,"text":"who are extraordinarily\ngood at whatever that is."},{"time":501825,"text":"If you don't know it already,\nthis is coming."},{"time":504000,"text":"The game industry is developing consoles"},{"time":506000,"text":"that are low-energy and that work\nwith the wireless phone networks"},{"time":509378,"text":"instead of broadband Internet,"},{"time":511228,"text":"so that gamers all over the world,"},{"time":513000,"text":"particularly in India, China,\nBrazil, can get online."},{"time":516848,"text":"They expect one billion more\ngamers in the next decade."},{"time":519498,"text":"It will bring us up to 1.5 billion gamers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":521957,"text":"So I've started to think about"},{"time":523449,"text":"what these games\nare making us virtuosos at."},{"time":525689,"text":"Here are the four things I came up with."},{"time":527664,"text":"The first is urgent optimism."},{"time":529648,"text":"OK, think of this\nas extreme self-motivation."},{"time":532743,"text":"Urgent optimism is the desire\nto act immediately"},{"time":535815,"text":"to tackle an obstacle,"},{"time":537496,"text":"combined with the belief that we have\na reasonable hope of success."},{"time":541743,"text":"Gamers always believe\nthat an epic win is possible,"},{"time":544453,"text":"and that it's always worth\ntrying, and trying now."},{"time":547182,"text":"Gamers don't sit around."},{"time":548773,"text":"Gamers are virtuosos\nat weaving a tight social fabric."},{"time":552853,"text":"There's a lot of interesting\nresearch that shows"},{"time":555134,"text":"we like people better\nafter we play a game with them,"},{"time":557714,"text":"even if they've beaten us badly."},{"time":559547,"text":"And the reason is, it takes a lot of trust\nto play a game with someone."},{"time":562913,"text":"We trust that they will spend\ntheir time with us,"},{"time":565229,"text":"that they will play by the same rules,"},{"time":567095,"text":"value the same goal,\nstay with the game until it's over."}]},{"cues":[{"time":570451,"text":"And so, playing a game together"},{"time":572043,"text":"actually builds up bonds\nand trust and cooperation."},{"time":575000,"text":"And we actually build stronger\nsocial relationships as a result."},{"time":579238,"text":"Blissful productivity. I love it."},{"time":581000,"text":"You know, there's a reason why\nthe average World of Warcraft gamer"},{"time":584318,"text":"plays for 22 hours a week --\nkind of a half-time job."},{"time":587000,"text":"It's because we know,\nwhen we're playing a game,"},{"time":589626,"text":"that we're actually happier working hard"},{"time":591999,"text":"than we are relaxing, or hanging out."},{"time":594274,"text":"We know that we are\noptimized as human beings,"},{"time":596576,"text":"to do hard and meaningful work."},{"time":598218,"text":"And gamers are willing\nto work hard all the time,"},{"time":601449,"text":"if they're given the right work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":603829,"text":"Finally: epic meaning."},{"time":605774,"text":"Gamers love to be attached\nto awe-inspiring missions"},{"time":609535,"text":"to human planetary-scale stories."},{"time":613571,"text":"So, just one bit of trivia\nthat helps put that into perspective:"},{"time":617335,"text":"So, you all know Wikipedia,\nbiggest wiki in the world."},{"time":621357,"text":"Second biggest wiki in the world,\nwith nearly 80,000 articles,"},{"time":625000,"text":"is the World of Warcraft wiki."},{"time":627000,"text":"Five million people use it every month."},{"time":629000,"text":"They have compiled more information\nabout World of Warcraft on the Internet"},{"time":632683,"text":"than any other topic covered\non any other wiki in the world."},{"time":635814,"text":"They are building an epic story."},{"time":637874,"text":"They are building an epic\nknowledge resource"},{"time":640120,"text":"about the World of Warcraft."}]},{"cues":[{"time":641676,"text":"Okay, so these are four superpowers\nthat add up to one thing:"},{"time":646000,"text":"Gamers are super-empowered\nhopeful individuals."},{"time":650795,"text":"These are people who believe\nthat they are individually capable"},{"time":654024,"text":"of changing the world."},{"time":655598,"text":"And the only problem is,"},{"time":657257,"text":"they believe that they are capable\nof changing virtual worlds"},{"time":660310,"text":"and not the real world."},{"time":662000,"text":"That's the problem\nthat I'm trying to solve."}]},{"cues":[{"time":664613,"text":"There's an economist\nnamed Edward Castronova."},{"time":667000,"text":"His work is brilliant."},{"time":668194,"text":"He looks at why people are investing\nso much time and energy"},{"time":671120,"text":"and money in online worlds."},{"time":673000,"text":"And he says,"},{"time":674207,"text":"\"We're witnessing what amounts to\nno less than a mass exodus"},{"time":677539,"text":"to virtual worlds and online\ngame environments.\""},{"time":680000,"text":"And he's an economist, so he's rational."},{"time":682213,"text":"And he says --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":683674,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":685341,"text":"Not like me, I'm a game\ndesigner; I'm exuberant."},{"time":687650,"text":"But he says that this makes perfect sense,"},{"time":691873,"text":"because gamers can achieve\nmore in online worlds"},{"time":694321,"text":"than they can in real life."},{"time":695671,"text":"They can have stronger\nsocial relationships in games"},{"time":698156,"text":"than they can have in real life;"},{"time":699735,"text":"they get better feedback\nand feel more rewarded in games"},{"time":702726,"text":"than they do in real life."},{"time":704000,"text":"So he says, for now it makes perfect sense"},{"time":706024,"text":"for gamers to spend more time\nin virtual worlds than the real world."},{"time":709623,"text":"Now, I also agree\nthat that is rational, for now."},{"time":713000,"text":"But it is not, by any means,\nan optimal situation."},{"time":716000,"text":"We have to start making\nthe real world work more like a game."}]},{"cues":[{"time":719377,"text":"I take my inspiration\nfrom something that happened"},{"time":722383,"text":"2,500 years ago."},{"time":724392,"text":"These are ancient dice,\nmade out of sheep's knuckles."},{"time":728000,"text":"Before we had awesome game controllers,"},{"time":730000,"text":"we had sheep's knuckles."},{"time":731837,"text":"And these represent\nthe first game equipment"},{"time":734929,"text":"designed by human beings,"},{"time":736819,"text":"and if you're familiar with the work\nof the ancient Greek historian Herodotus,"},{"time":740587,"text":"you might know this history,"},{"time":742120,"text":"which is the history\nof who invented games and why."},{"time":745716,"text":"Herodotus says that games,\nparticularly dice games,"},{"time":748584,"text":"were invented in the kingdom of Lydia,"},{"time":751000,"text":"during a time of famine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":752833,"text":"Apparently, there was such a severe famine"},{"time":755196,"text":"that the king of Lydia decided\nthey had to do something crazy."},{"time":759000,"text":"People were suffering.\nPeople were fighting."},{"time":761120,"text":"It was an extreme situation,\nthey needed an extreme solution."},{"time":765000,"text":"So, according to Herodotus,\nthey invented dice games,"},{"time":768000,"text":"and they set up a kingdom-wide policy:"},{"time":771000,"text":"On one day, everybody would eat,"},{"time":773606,"text":"and on the next day,\neverybody would play games."},{"time":776000,"text":"And they would be so immersed\nin playing the dice games,"},{"time":778658,"text":"because games are so engaging,"},{"time":780126,"text":"and immerse us in such satisfying,\nblissful productivity,"},{"time":783362,"text":"they would ignore the fact\nthat they had no food to eat."},{"time":786100,"text":"And then on the next day,\nthey would play games;"},{"time":788410,"text":"and on the next day, they would eat."}]},{"cues":[{"time":790310,"text":"And according to Herodotus,"},{"time":792000,"text":"they passed 18 years this way,"},{"time":794000,"text":"surviving through a famine,"},{"time":795763,"text":"by eating on one day,\nand playing games on the next."},{"time":798453,"text":"Now, this is exactly, I think,\nhow we're using games today."},{"time":802726,"text":"We're using games to escape\nreal-world suffering --"},{"time":805457,"text":"we're using games to get away"},{"time":807072,"text":"from everything that's broken\nin the real environment,"},{"time":809685,"text":"everything that's not satisfying\nabout real life,"},{"time":812255,"text":"and we're getting what we need from games."}]},{"cues":[{"time":814377,"text":"But it doesn't have to end there."},{"time":816000,"text":"This is really exciting."},{"time":818000,"text":"According to Herodotus, after 18 years\nthe famine wasn't getting better,"},{"time":823000,"text":"so the king decided they would\nplay one final dice game."},{"time":827408,"text":"They divided the entire kingdom in half."},{"time":830169,"text":"They played one dice game,"},{"time":831901,"text":"and the winners of that game\ngot to go on an epic adventure."},{"time":835344,"text":"They would leave Lydia,"},{"time":837000,"text":"and they would go out in search\nof a new place to live,"},{"time":839999,"text":"leaving behind just enough people"},{"time":842223,"text":"to survive on the resources\nthat were available,"},{"time":844540,"text":"and hopefully to take their civilization\nsomewhere else where they could thrive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":848389,"text":"Now, this sounds crazy, right?"},{"time":850312,"text":"But recently, DNA evidence\nhas shown that the Etruscans,"},{"time":854754,"text":"who then led to the Roman Empire,"},{"time":856540,"text":"actually share the same DNA\nas the ancient Lydians."},{"time":859469,"text":"And so, recently,\nscientists have suggested"},{"time":862000,"text":"that Herodotus' crazy\nstory is actually true."},{"time":864421,"text":"And geologists have found\nevidence of a global cooling"},{"time":867414,"text":"that lasted for nearly 20 years,\nthat could have explained the famine."},{"time":871174,"text":"So this crazy story might be true."},{"time":873428,"text":"They might have actually saved\ntheir culture by playing games,"},{"time":877348,"text":"escaping to games for 18 years,"},{"time":879294,"text":"and then been so inspired,"},{"time":880770,"text":"and knew so much about\nhow to come together with games,"},{"time":883476,"text":"that they actually saved\nthe entire civilization that way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":886237,"text":"Okay, we can do that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":887426,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":888472,"text":"We've been playing Warcraft since 1994."},{"time":890834,"text":"That was the first real-time strategy\ngame from the World of Warcraft series."},{"time":894529,"text":"That was 16 years ago."},{"time":896340,"text":"They played dice games for 18 years,"},{"time":898157,"text":"we've been playing Warcraft for 16 years."},{"time":900427,"text":"I say we are ready for our own epic game."},{"time":903609,"text":"Now, they had half the civilization\ngo off in search of a new world,"},{"time":908243,"text":"so that's where I get my 21 billion\nhours a week of game-play from."},{"time":912116,"text":"Let's get half of us to agree"},{"time":914000,"text":"to spend an hour a day playing games,"},{"time":916000,"text":"until we solve real-world problems."}]},{"cues":[{"time":917866,"text":"Now, I know you're asking,"},{"time":919462,"text":"\"How are we going to solve\nreal-world problems in games?\""},{"time":922165,"text":"Well, that's what I've devoted\nmy work to over the past few years,"},{"time":925300,"text":"at the Institute for the Future."},{"time":927000,"text":"We have this banner\nin our offices in Palo Alto,"},{"time":929310,"text":"and it expresses our view of how\nwe should try to relate to the future."},{"time":933445,"text":"We do not want to try\nto predict the future."},{"time":935730,"text":"What we want to do is make the future."},{"time":937786,"text":"We want to imagine\nthe best-case scenario outcome,"},{"time":940302,"text":"and then we want to empower people\nto make that outcome a reality."},{"time":944000,"text":"We want to imagine epic wins,"},{"time":946000,"text":"and then give people the means\nto achieve the epic win."}]},{"cues":[{"time":949000,"text":"I'm just going to very briefly show you\nthree games that I've made"},{"time":952122,"text":"that are an attempt to give people\nthe means to create epic wins"},{"time":955202,"text":"in their own futures."},{"time":956559,"text":"This is World Without Oil."},{"time":958000,"text":"We made this game in 2007."},{"time":959715,"text":"This is an online game"},{"time":961097,"text":"in which you try to survive\nan oil shortage."},{"time":964507,"text":"The oil shortage is fictional,"},{"time":966126,"text":"but we put enough online content out there"},{"time":969000,"text":"for you to believe that it's real,"},{"time":970704,"text":"and to live your real life\nas if we've run out of oil."},{"time":973614,"text":"So when you come to the game,"},{"time":975074,"text":"you sign up, tell us where you live,"},{"time":977027,"text":"and then we give you\nreal-time news videos,"},{"time":979391,"text":"data feeds that show you\nexactly how much oil costs,"},{"time":982535,"text":"what's not available, how food\nsupply is being affected,"},{"time":985288,"text":"how transportation is being affected,"},{"time":987146,"text":"if schools are closed, if there's rioting,"},{"time":989241,"text":"and you have to figure out\nhow you would live your real life"},{"time":992114,"text":"as if this were true."},{"time":993377,"text":"And then we ask you to blog about it,"},{"time":995200,"text":"to post videos, to post photos."}]},{"cues":[{"time":997000,"text":"We piloted this game\nwith 1,700 players in 2007,"},{"time":1000424,"text":"and we've tracked them\nfor the three years since."},{"time":1002781,"text":"And I can tell you that this\nis a transformative experience."},{"time":1005882,"text":"Nobody wants to change how they live,"},{"time":1007789,"text":"just because it's good for the world,\nor because we're supposed to."},{"time":1011518,"text":"But if you immerse them\nin an epic adventure"},{"time":1014000,"text":"and tell them, \"We've run out of oil."},{"time":1016000,"text":"This is an amazing story\nand adventure for you to go on."},{"time":1019289,"text":"Challenge yourself to see\nhow you would survive,\""},{"time":1022000,"text":"most of our players\nhave kept up the habits"},{"time":1024072,"text":"that they learned in this game."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1025892,"text":"So for the next world-saving game,"},{"time":1028000,"text":"we decided to aim higher --\nbigger problem than just peak oil."},{"time":1031495,"text":"We did a game called Superstruct\nat the Institute for the Future."},{"time":1034901,"text":"And the premise was,\na supercomputer has calculated"},{"time":1038000,"text":"that humans have only 23 years\nleft on the planet."},{"time":1041000,"text":"This supercomputer was called"},{"time":1042573,"text":"the Global Extinction\nAwareness System, of course."},{"time":1045334,"text":"We asked people to come online --"},{"time":1047000,"text":"almost like a Jerry Bruckheimer movie."},{"time":1049123,"text":"You know Jerry Bruckheimer\nmovies, you form a dream team --"},{"time":1052000,"text":"you've got the astronaut,\nthe scientist, the ex-convict,"},{"time":1054775,"text":"and they all have something\nto do to save the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1057236,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1058267,"text":"But in our game, instead of just having\nfive people on the dream team,"},{"time":1061679,"text":"we said, \"Everybody's on the dream team,"},{"time":1063632,"text":"and it's your job to invent\nthe future of energy,"},{"time":1066000,"text":"the future of food, the future of health,"},{"time":1068000,"text":"the future of security and the future\nof the social safety net.\""},{"time":1071072,"text":"We had 8,000 people\nplay that game for eight weeks."},{"time":1073685,"text":"They came up with 500\ninsanely creative solutions"},{"time":1076757,"text":"that you can go online,\nGoogle \"Superstruct,\" and see."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1079611,"text":"So, finally, the last game,"},{"time":1081000,"text":"we're launching it March 3rd."},{"time":1082480,"text":"This is a game done\nwith the World Bank Institute."},{"time":1084938,"text":"If you complete the game,"},{"time":1086166,"text":"you will be certified\nby the World Bank Institute"},{"time":1089000,"text":"as a Social Innovator, class of 2010."},{"time":1091722,"text":"Working with universities\nall over sub-Saharan Africa,"},{"time":1095000,"text":"and we are inviting them\nto learn social innovation skills."},{"time":1098000,"text":"We've got a graphic novel,\nwe've got leveling up"},{"time":1101000,"text":"in skills like local insight,\nknowledge networking,"},{"time":1104000,"text":"sustainability,\nvision and resourcefulness."},{"time":1106485,"text":"I would like to invite all of you"},{"time":1108096,"text":"to please share this game\nwith young people,"},{"time":1110255,"text":"anywhere in the world,\nparticularly in developing areas,"},{"time":1113000,"text":"who might benefit from coming together"},{"time":1115222,"text":"to try to start to imagine their own\nsocial enterprises to save the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1119750,"text":"So, I'm going to wrap up now."},{"time":1121766,"text":"I want to ask a question."},{"time":1123536,"text":"What do you think happens next?"},{"time":1125361,"text":"We've got all these amazing gamers,\nwe've got these games"},{"time":1128053,"text":"that are kind of pilots\nof what we might do,"},{"time":1130189,"text":"but none of them\nhave saved the real world yet."},{"time":1132419,"text":"Well I hope you will agree with me\nthat gamers are a human resource"},{"time":1136792,"text":"that we can use to do real-world work,"},{"time":1139000,"text":"that games are a powerful\nplatform for change."},{"time":1141577,"text":"We have all these amazing superpowers:"},{"time":1143593,"text":"blissful productivity, the ability\nto weave a tight social fabric,"},{"time":1147000,"text":"this feeling of urgent optimism\nand the desire for epic meaning."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1151000,"text":"I really hope that we can come together\nto play games that matter,"},{"time":1154533,"text":"to survive on this planet\nfor another century."},{"time":1156783,"text":"That's my hope, that you will join me\nin making and playing games like this."},{"time":1160459,"text":"When I look forward to the next decade,\nI know two things for sure:"},{"time":1164283,"text":"that we can make\nany future we can imagine,"},{"time":1167000,"text":"and we can play any games\nwe want, so I say:"},{"time":1170134,"text":"Let the world-changing games begin."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1171874,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1173056,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}